cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and dependency parsing. It may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes a novel transition system and dynamic oracle for parsing, which involves machine learning and AI techniques. Additionally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the Covington algorithm and its variants. Finally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as neural networks are commonly used in dependency parsing.
